snippet.textDisplay:
In the future I'd suggest placing your corn flakes into a extra large zip type plastic bag then ensure no air is inside; zip it shut .. use a rolling pin to make it super fine.
If you have a food processor you can use that in place of the other technique. I'd encourage you to add different flavors to the crunchy texture.. maybe walnuts & shelled pumpkin seeds cut down to a sand-like texture, along with the ground cinnamon spice. If your feeling interesting you could try shredded coconut flakes, whatever suits you.
